title: The Art and Life of Georgia O'Keeffe (Art Ebook).pdf
description:
Crown | 1985 | Pdf | Eng | ISBN10 051755058X | 192 pages | 26.5 MB

"Georgia O'Keeffe is a unique figure in contemporary American art. Her art is an individual one, expressing personal emotions and perceptions in a style that combines strength and crystalline clarity... She was a pioneer of native modern an, and through her long career she has continued to make some of the most original contributions to the art of our time." So wrote Lloyd Goodrich, Director Emeritus of the Whitney Museum of American Art, on the occasion of Georgia O'Keeffe's 1970 retrospective exhibition
